description: A jelly-like medicine that recovers 50% HP to a single ally.
name: Life Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that can heal wounds.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
It has become a standard in recovery medicine.
A must have for adventurers.>

description: A jelly-like medicine that recovers 100% HP to a single ally.
name: Super Life Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that can heal wounds.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
It is extremely potent as recovery medicine,
but the price is also nothing to scoff at.>

description: A jelly-like medicine that recovers 50% SP to a single ally.
name: Energy Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that can restore energy.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
Energy is always required to unleash skills and magic.
This jelly helps with restoring that energy,
but the cost for production is quite high due to its Mana component.>

description: A jelly-like medicine that recovers 100% SP to a single ally.
name: Super Energy Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that can restore energy.

Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
It is extremely potent as recovery medicine,
but the price is also nothing to scoff at.>

description:
A jelly-like medicine that removes ailments from a single ally.
Red-bordered ailments cannot be removed.
name: Healthy Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that treats abnormalities.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
It heals only the physical ailment,
and has no effect on any associated emotional trauma.>

description: Jelly-like medicine that removes Stat Down effects from a single ally.
name: Power Jelly
note:
<dPlnText:Medicine that treats abnormalities.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
It heals only the physical ailment,
and has no effect on any associated emotional trauma.>

description: Mana-infused liquid that revives a single ally and recovers 25% HP.
name: Mana Pot
note:
<dPlnText:A liquid that revives those who are Unable to Fight.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
Being Unable to Fight and dying are completely different.
In a sense, the word 'revive' is false advertisement.>

description: Mana-infused liquid that revives a single ally and recovers 100% HP.
name: Super Mana Pot
note:
<dPlnText:A liquid that revives those who are Unable to Fight.
Created by the Aurum Company global organization.
　
Being Unable to Fight and dying are completely different.
In a sense, the word 'revive' is false advertisement.>

description: Medicine that restores 100% HP and SP to a single ally.
name: Ultimate
note:
<dPlnText:A special medicine created by a first-class alchemist.
　
Not exactly something you can get easily,
so save it for when you really need it.>

description: Medicine that restores 100% HP and SP to all allies.
name: Super Ultimate
note:
<dPlnText:A special medicine created by a first-class alchemist.
　
Not exactly something you can get easily,
but the regret of using it is also hard to reconcile with.>

description: A mysterious seed that raises the level of a single ally by 1.
name: Vivid Mana Seed
note:
<ExpIncrease:1000000>
<levelUpStop>
<dPlnText:Something with awazing potential for growth.
This is but one form of mana,
taking on the form of a seed.
　
The power to promote growth, the essence of Mana.
Without it, the world itself would come to collapse.>

description: A fruit that increases all stats of a single ally by 5.
name: Fruit of Growth
note:
<dPlnText:Eating improves the basic abilities of the body.
　
This is Mana, taking the form of a fruit.
Should you consume it, your strength will grow accordingly.
　
No taste, negative texture.>

description: A bomb that deals ~500 Magical Wave DMG to a single enemy.
name: Wave Bomb
note:
<dPlnText:A bomb containing Wave magic.
　
The Wave attribute is Mana's power in its purest form.
It'll work on most opponents, but due to its nature
it cannot bypass any magical countermeasures.>

description:
A bomb that removes beneficial effects from enemies.
Red-bordered effects cannot be removed.
name: Shit Bomb
note:
<dPlnText:A bomb made of hardened monster excrement.
　
This substance has a mana-inhibiting property,
negating strengthening powers of anyone coated by it.
　
Make sure to handle it with care.
You're not getting away with it lightly if it goes off.>

description: Eggs that increase Ino's Mana Brilliance by 100.
name: Egg of Life
note:
<OrderId:15>
<dPlnText:An egg-shaped mass.
Swallowing it increases the strength of Mana.
　
Absolutely tasteless.>

description:
A drink that restores 100% HP to a single ally.
Cannot be used during battle.
name: Dairy Milk
note:
<OrderId:15>
<dPlnText:A specialty found during the journey.
Can be purchased at Ront's Mana Ranch.
　
The monster's milk is sweet and tasty,
but a man drinking it would find his crotch burning up.>

description:
A cloth that restores 50% HP to a single ally.
Cannot be used during battle.
name: Cozy Cloth
note:
<OrderId:15>
<dPlnText:A specialty found during the journey.
Can be purchased in Certilt's Spiral City.
　
No matter the time in place, just by lying on this,
you can be guaranteed a relaxing rest.>

description:
Salted meat that restores 25 TP to a single ally.
Cannot be used during battle.
name: Hunter's Rations
note:
<OrderId:15>
<dPlnText:A specialty found during the journey.
Can be purchased at the Hunter's Rest in Tarvilal.
　
Surprisingly delicious and high quality.
Meat lovers will most definitely enjoy this.>

description: Souvenirs sold in the entertainment district.
name: Souvenir
note:
<OrderId:15>
<dPlnText:A specialty found during the journey.
Can be purchased in Torrion's Red Light District.
　
It has no good personal use, so
it might be best to give it to someone.>

description: イノの称号
name: 称号１

description: A beautiful fragment, though ultimately worthless.
name: Stardust
note:
<dPlnText:Stardust that fell from space.
Found in various areas in Parlates.
　
This is burnt out life, a remnant of Mana.
For the truth of immortality has no effect on the world's origin.>

description:
Immediately moves to \C[17]Earthless Ainoa\C[0].
Use this item while exploring by pressing \C[17]C\C[0].
name: Wing Stone
note:
<dPlnText:A tool to return to Ainoa, the center of Parlates.
Wish and hold tight, and it shall come true.
　
The Reason of Wings that connects the stars,
footprints of their Lord, the history of the world.>

description:
Displays the Events screen. 
Use this item while exploring by pressing \C[17]D\C[0].
name: Adventurer's Note
note:
<dPlnText:A memoir all adventurers possess.
Writing down the story so far, and what is to come.
　
Some travel without an Adventurer's Note,
but those are rather known as wanderers.>

description:
All allies recover 50% HP. Remaining uses: \C[24]\V[21]\C[0].
Use this item while exploring by pressing \C[17]V\C[0].
name: Mana Bottle
note:
<dPlnText:A bottle filled with water containing Mana.
A tool that originated in the valley country Alzet.
　
It's become a widespread topic for exploration,
but doesn't see nearly as much actual usage.>

description: You may choose whether or not to gain EXP.
name: Challenger's Mirror
note:
<dPlnText:A hand mirror with strange powers.
Temporarily deny combat experience from anyone who projects it.
　
Effort without reward is but futile lunacy,
but there are oddballs who may appreciate that.>

description: When used in battle, become defeated.
name: Symbol of Defeat
note:
<dPlnText:The curse of those who cannot win.
The user and his allies are invited to certain defeat.
　
It's such an obvious trap nobody'd use it,
but there could be something to gain from losing.>

description: A lantern that illuminates the surroundings.
name: White Flame Lantern
note:
<dPlnText:A magically illuminated lantern.
Absolutely indispensable in dark places.
　
There are adventurers who grope their way through,
but the experienced never underestimates the dark.>

description: Increases the usages of Mana Bottles.
name: Life Bottle
note:
<dPlnText:A special vial that stores Mana.
Unreliable, but it does count towards being a Mana Bottle.
　
The Life Bottle is a pretty common tool,
but this one is a little different from the norm.>

description: A vessel that shines faintly.
name: Mana Vessel
note:
<dPlnText:A vessel entrusted to the Lord of Reason.
The most supreme tool, crafted by a most supreme witch.
　
The stars give birth to Mana, which is returned to the world.
That is how Parlates was created.>

description: A shining gleam containing the Light attribute.
name: Star Mark
note:
<dPlnText:A tool against the darkness.
One of the supreme witch's great creations.
　
Darkness itself is inherently dangerous.
That, in itself, is its nature.>

description: A part plucked from a Dryad.
name: Dryad Fragment
note:
<dPlnText:A strangely-shaped flower.
Can be plucked from well-developed Dryads.
　
Dryads can produce Mana as it grows,
which in turn makes them grow faster.
　
In the Age of Myth, some witches would
name this as the Flower of Dahna.>

description: Mechanical parts.
name: Acoustic Transducer
note:
<dPlnText:A part of a crumbling machine.
You can hear voices if you put your ear to it.
　
There must be an owner around, somewhere.>

description: A stone key used by witches to seal something.
name: Key of Knowledge
note:
<dPlnText:One of the tools of magi.
Used to seal a certain something.
　
The keyhole lies on a moron's statue.
Provide knowledge, expose the truth.>

description: A dry twig.
name: Tree Branch
note:
<dPlnText:A branch from a shore nobody knows of.
No particular characteristics of note.
　
It is completely lacking in water,
and is therefore highly flammable.>

description: Long plant life.
name: Tough Vine
note:
<dPlnText:A wild plant from a shore nobody knows of.
Super long and sturdy.
　
Perhaps there is a use for it.>

description: A bunch of vines.
name: Bundled Vines
note:
<dPlnText:A bunch of vines tied together with rope.
Cannot be torn apart easily.
　
Appears to be suitable for climbing high places.>

description: Caught fish.
name: Fish
note:
<dPlnText:A fish from a sea nobody knows of.
Appears to be edible.
　
The taste is very bland, though.>

description: An object that looks like a key.
name: Keylike Object
note:
<dPlnText:Something that looks like a key,
but also can be not a key.
　
The only place to try it out is the mansion.>

description: A handle meant to be attached somewhere.
name: Handle
note:
<dPlnText:A metal handle.
You can attach it somewhere to operate something.
　
Leaves a lot of dust in your hand.
Must've been abandoned for a while.>

description: Luggage that must be delivered to the Mana Ranch.
name: Ranch Luggage
note:
<dPlnText:A large package suddenly entrusted to you.
Deliver it to the Mana Ranch.>

description: A key to a hidden tailor in Spiral City.
name: Tailor's Key
note:
<dPlnText:A key with a distinctive design.
It was once common in the City of Clothing.
　
The Tailor has some old residents.>

description: Key to the Lavigny Barricade Prison.
name: Key of Lavigny
note:
<dPlnText:Dirty black key.
Used to open the normal prisons of the Barricade Prison.
　
Though it has fallen under someone's care,
the prowling monsters still cling to old ties.>

description: Held by a monster in the Barricade Prison's deepest part.
name: Tarnished Ornament
note:
<dPlnText:An ornament in disrepair.
The luxurious finish now appears miserable.
　
When the family fractures under suspicion and punishment,
the damage was directed to their beloved daughters.
　
"That is the spark of conflict.
　No other choice but to throw them away.">

description: A key to the Hybrid Lab.
name: Lab Key
note:
<dPlnText:A key with a complex shape.
Able to open a cage in the laboratory.
　
It is located at the back of the dump, but
half of it collapsed and crashed to another star.>

description: A hairpin that was in the hand of a corpse.
name: Old Hairpin
note:
<dPlnText:A hairpin tucked away with care.
Old, but not in bad condition.
　
This is a certain demon's lost item.
Let's deliver it to its owner.>

description: The thing that was sunk in the Shoeba Oceans.
name: Sharp Edge
note:
<dPlnText:Black inconspicuous blade.
Found in Sous Shoeba.
　
Sharp and pointed, but badly damaged,
unfit for becoming a weapon.>

description: A gift for the unparalleled.
name: Proof of Conquest
note:
<dPlnText:Medal of honor for the unparalleled.
　
Purely a recognition of achievement,
and nothing more.

It's value is only in the difficulty of its attainment.>

description: An inorganic stone that serves as a base for Engraving.
name: Earthless Stone
note:
<dPlnText:An eerily inorganic stone.
Embraces power to become a Symbol to engrave.
　
Can be obtained after a difficult battle.>

description: A mass that is the source of Skill Crystals.
name: Clear Lump
note:
<dPlnText:A transparent blob.
Embraces techniques to become Skill Crystals.
　
Can be obtained after a difficult battle.>

description: A rainbow-colored branch that holds memories.
name: Branch of Memory
note:
<dPlnText:A rainbow-colored substance
 shaped like a branch.

 Dropped by entities in the memory area.>

description: A fragment that becomes material for Engraving.
name: Origin Fragment
note:
<dPlnText:A fragment necessary to engrave an Earthless Stone.
　
A fragment of Mana, a crystal of vitality.
Handle it right and harness its power.>

description: A large shard that becomes material for Engraving.
name: Origin Shard
note:
<dPlnText:A fragment necessary to engrave an Earthless Stone.
　
A fragment of Mana, a crystal of vitality.
Handle it right and harness its power.>

name: Origin Chunk
note:

note:

note:

note:

description: A fragment that becomes material for Engraving.
name: Rainbow Fragment
note:
<dPlnText:A fragment necessary to engrave an Earthless Stone.
　
A fragment of Mana, a crystal of vitality.
Handle it right and harness its power.>

description: Substances that form memories.
name: Reason of Solitude
note:
<dPlnText:Skill Crystal-like substance.
Forms the memory of the Lord of Reason.

This is one of the Reasons
which influences all of Parlates.>

name: Reason of Sacrifice
note:

This is one of the Reasons

name: Reason of Breeze
note:
<dPlnText:Skill Crystal-like substance.
Forms the memory of the Lord of Reason.

This is one of the Reasons
which influences all of Parlates.>

description: One of the memories in the sea of Parlates.
name: Memories of Light and Dark
note:
<dPlnText:Shaped memories harboring light and darkness.
　
The more memorable it is,
the more stable it takes form.>

name: Skill Memory
note:
<dPlnText:Stone tablets that store special Mana.
Memories of demons are engraved on it.
　
A plant named Dahna has the power to crystallize Mana,
and awaken the memories of monsters.>
